Phase 7 #15 (legacy-socket-retirement) shipped on 2026-05-19:
- Tier 2 subagent-driven execution (Opus 4.7 controller + Sonnet implementers/reviewers per task). Two thrash recoveries: Task 5 (router rewire + reject deletion + test creation) and Task 12 (governance docs across 2217 lines) — controller absorbed both inline after the Sonnet 30K-budget breach. User picked (legacy-socket-retirement) from recommended-next slot after #14.
- NEW `apps/web/src/server/socket/calls.ts` (53 lines) — `attachCallHandlers({io, socket})` joins `${orgId}:call:incoming` + `${orgId}:call:rejected` via `joinOrgChannel` on connect, listens for client-emitted `call:reject` events with server-resolved caller identity (reads `socket.data.session.userId`), broadcasts `call:rejected {callId, reason: "declined"}` org-scoped via `emitToOrg`. NO ROSTER — calls are ephemeral per-event transmissions unlike Phase 7 #11/#14 presence + in-call engines. Server-fixed `reason: "declined"`; `"unavailable"` reserved for future auto-timeout flows.
- NEW `apps/web/src/server/socket/calls.test.ts` (122 lines, 8 RED→GREEN) — session-guard no-op when `socket.data.session` undefined; both channels joined on connect; valid relay; 5 malformed-payload rejects (non-object, missing callId, non-string callId, empty-string callId, callId.length > 128). Hand-rolled MinimalSocket + IOServer fakes per [[socket-revalidation-test-pattern]].
- NEW `apps/web/src/lib/calls/incoming-call-handler.ts` (43 lines) — pure helper `attachIncomingCallHandler(socket, callbacks)` mirroring `lib/presence/in-call-handler.ts` byte-for-byte. Exports `MinimalIncomingCallSocketTarget` + `RejectedPayload` + `IncomingCallCallbacks` + `IncomingCallDisposer` types. Node-testable per [[pure-helper-extraction-pattern]].
- NEW `apps/web/src/lib/calls/incoming-call-handler.test.ts` (107 lines, 5 RED→GREEN) — register both listeners, onIncoming fires, onRejected fires (declined), disposer unwires + no-callbacks-after-dispose, onRejected fires (unavailable union member).
- NEW `apps/web/src/server/trpc/routers/calls.test.ts` (156 lines, 3 RED→GREEN) — happy path: emit via `emitToOrg` with org-scoped channel + recipientDeptId in payload; department not found → NOT_FOUND, no emit; `getIO()` returns null → returns connection details, no emit (graceful degradation for build/test contexts). Created from scratch — file did not exist before.
- MODIFIED `apps/web/src/server/socket/server.ts` (+17 lines) — module-level `let ioInstance: IOServer | null = null` + `export function getIO()` accessor + idempotent guard `if (ioInstance !== null) return ioInstance` at top of `createSocketServer` (HMR safety mirroring legacy `initSocketServer` behavior) + `ioInstance = io` after `new IOServer(...)` + `attachCallHandlers({io, socket})` in `io.on("connection")` alongside presence + in-call.
- MODIFIED `apps/web/src/server/trpc/routers/calls.ts` (-25 net) — switched import from `@/lib/socket/server` (dead) to `@/server/socket/server` + `@/server/socket/channels`; inlined `emitToOrg(io, ctx.organizationId, "call:incoming", {callId, callerName, callerDepartment, roomName, recipientDeptId})` replacing legacy `emitIncomingCall` call; DELETED entire `reject` mutation (was lines 81-98, ~18 lines) — zero call sites; rejection now flows through `socket.emit("call:reject")` in the dialog.
- MODIFIED `apps/web/src/lib/livekit/types.ts` (+1 line) — added `recipientDeptId: string` field to `IncomingCallPayload` for future client-side dept filter (TODO follow-up in #16).
- MODIFIED `apps/web/src/lib/socket/types.ts` (-17 lines) — deleted `presence:subscribe` + `presence:heartbeat` + `presence:update` events (orphaned by Phase 7 #11/#12 migration + legacy server deletion); deleted `subscribedDepartmentIds: Set<string>` field on `SocketData`; deleted `callIncomingRoom` + `callerRoom` helper exports; deleted `PresenceState` import (only used by deleted `presence:update`).
- MODIFIED `apps/web/src/components/call/incoming-call-dialog.tsx` (-55+30 net) — drop `import { io, type Socket } from "socket.io-client"`; drop `SOCKET_URL` constant + `socketRef` ref; switch to `useSocketOptional()` for shared socket reference + `attachIncomingCallHandler(socket, {onIncoming, onRejected})` for listener wiring. Now subscribes to BOTH `call:incoming` AND `call:rejected` (former was the only event handled by raw io() before, but raw io() was hitting a 503 placeholder so neither actually worked end-to-end). Reject button emits via shared socket: `socket?.emit("call:reject", {callId: payload.callId})`. TODO follow-up (Phase 7 #16 candidate): filter onIncoming by `incoming.recipientDeptId === currentUser.boundDeptId`.
- DELETED `apps/web/src/lib/socket/server.ts` (159 lines) — `initSocketServer()` had ZERO call sites in `apps/web/src`. Phantom `server/custom-server.ts` referenced in module comments never existed (abandoned at Phase 7 #8e-1 in favor of separate-SOCKET_PORT pattern via `instrumentation.ts`). `getIO()` always returned null in production — incoming-call had been broken end-to-end since the architectural pivot. Phase 7 #15 was the FIRST real implementation, not a migration.
- DELETED `apps/web/src/app/api/socket/route.ts` (39 lines) — Next.js Route Handler that returned 503; intentional placeholder for the abandoned `server/custom-server.ts` path. Route Handlers cannot perform WebSocket upgrades anyway. The raw `io()` connection from `incoming-call-dialog` had been hitting this 503 since Phase 7 #8e-1.
- 16 new RED→GREEN cases (test suite 144→160). pnpm typecheck ✓ 0 errors 8 packages. pnpm lint ✓ 0 errors (2 pre-existing warnings unchanged). pnpm build ✓ 22 routes + middleware 141kB compiled in ~51s (MANDATORY per [[instrumentation-edge-stub-required]] — calls.ts joins createSocketServer import chain). pnpm audit --audit-level=critical ✓ exit 0 (Phase 7 #9 + #10 still in effect; 1 HIGH = documented nodemailer per [[nodemailer-cve-mitigation]]).
- Two-stage review (Rule 25): Stage 1 spec PASS (10/10 — attachCallHandlers exists with locked signature, wired in connection block, getIO singleton + idempotent guard, calls.initiate imports from new paths, emit includes recipientDeptId, reject mutation deleted, both legacy files removed, types cleanup verified by grep, dialog uses useSocketOptional + attachIncomingCallHandler, reject button via shared socket); Stage 2 quality PASS (8/8 — zero any, no unjustified assertions, TDD RED→GREEN, blast-radius only, conventional commits, event-name consistency across 4 files, disposer mirrors precedent, Edge-build green).
- 0 new typed lessons logged — existing patterns covered everything ([[pure-helper-extraction-pattern]], [[socket-revalidation-test-pattern]], [[event-handler-disposer-test-pattern]], [[instrumentation-edge-stub-required]], [[nodemailer-cve-mitigation]]). New process observation worth noting (not encoded as typed lesson yet): Sonnet subagents thrash on multi-file integration tasks (Task 5 router rewire) and on governance-file edits spanning 2000+ lines (Task 12). Future tickets with similar shape should either pre-bake context aggressively (one bash with all relevant file excerpts in one tool call) or stay inline. Reviewer subagents stayed within budget throughout.
- 12 branch commits before squash: `9a54051` test+impl client handler, `45be0db` exports + 5th test, `6d7b109` FakeSocket cast, `a2fcb97` server calls handler, `64d560a` JSDoc fix, `8c49ea4` getIO + wire, `6dceb35` idempotent guard, `4c8d9ed` recipientDeptId on IncomingCallPayload, `14893b0` router rewire + delete reject mutation, `57499bb` delete legacy files, `13ad407` dialog migration, `1eec9c1` types cleanup.
